HEADWORD: Quittor
<hw>Quit"tor</hw> <pr>(kw⟦icr⟧t"t⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Perhaps for <ets>quitture</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Far.)</fld> <def>A
chronic abscess, or fistula of the coronet, in a horse's foot, resulting
from inflammation of the tissues investing the coffin bone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

